00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,900
=Daughter of Fortune=

2
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,460
(Adapted from the novel
"Phoenix Palace Dream" by Lan Jiujiu)

3
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:08,460
=Episode 16=

4
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,439
Sir, you've been competing in Daliang
for two days now.

5
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,480
Have you seen any scholar here

6
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,760
refuse to admit defeat?

7
00:01:15,079 --> 00:01:16,640
You simply can't accept losing.

8
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:17,959
- Sore loser!
- Sore loser!

9
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:19,359
The people of Jin are unethical.

10
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:20,840
Shameless!

11
00:01:21,319 --> 00:01:21,959
Fine.

12
00:01:22,439 --> 00:01:23,120
I concede.

13
00:01:24,079 --> 00:01:24,760
Come.

14
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:26,280
Pour the tea.

15
00:01:35,959 --> 00:01:38,560
- Good!
- Good!

16
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:43,319
(Tinglan Palace)
Lady Shen,

17
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,560
His Majesty asked me
to deliver this to you.

18
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,120
It's your reward
for winning the poetry gathering.

19
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:48,680
Thank you.

20
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,799
Look, Young Lady.

21
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:57,760
It's a golden hairpin.

22
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:06,519
Young Lady, let me put it on for you.

23
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,240
(He gave me a gold hairpin.)

24
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,800
(I should prepare a gift in return.)

25
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:16,140
(Yuehui Pavilion)

26
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:19,840
It's finally almost done.

27
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:21,990
I should still have time
to give it to him tonight.

28
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,120
Mm.

29
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,120
It's beautiful.

30
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,319
It's a lively fox.

31
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:27,599
If it's a gift for His Majesty,

32
00:02:27,759 --> 00:02:30,319
why carve a fox instead
of mandarin ducks?

33
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:33,000
People say foxes bewitch their masters,

34
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:34,280
but they don't know

35
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,879
that foxes stay loyal to one mate
for life.

36
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,080
People also say

37
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,960
they envy mandarin ducks
more than immortals,

38
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:43,240
but they don't know

39
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:45,360
mandarin ducks
change mates every year.

40
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,360
They're fickle.

41
00:02:46,370 --> 00:02:48,159
I didn't know
mandarin ducks are unfaithful.

42
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,919
They are.

43
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,240
His Majesty always says
I'm a devious fox,

44
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:54,280
but he doesn't realize

45
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:55,719
he's actually complimenting me.

46
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:57,120
Foxes are good.

47
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:02,520
There's something I've wanted to say.

48
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:03,240
Yes?

49
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:05,360
I've observed His Majesty before.

50
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,639
I think he truly cares about you.

51
00:03:11,199 --> 00:03:12,719
Perhaps a little.

52
00:03:14,879 --> 00:03:15,960
I'm not sure.

53
00:03:17,599 --> 00:03:18,840
So what if he does?

54
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,390
No one can live a lifetime
relying on another person's sincerity.

55
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,800
When you were back in Chizhou,

56
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,680
you used to envy the loving couples

57
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,560
in huaben.

58
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,479
But since entering the palace,

59
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,360
you've become so burdened with worries.

60
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,159
I want to help you,

61
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,599
but I don't know how.

62
00:03:37,159 --> 00:03:38,039
I'm fine.

63
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:39,000
I mean it.

64
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,400
Don't put too much pressure on yourself.

65
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,159
You can get along with His Majesty

66
00:03:44,159 --> 00:03:45,960
like an ordinary married couple.

67
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,439
Maybe you'd be happier that way.

68
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:49,800
I'm getting along well with him.

69
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,840
But being like an ordinary couple

70
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,080
is impossible.

71
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,240
He's the Emperor, after all.

72
00:03:58,439 --> 00:03:59,439
Besides,

73
00:03:59,879 --> 00:04:01,400
his moods change without warning.

74
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,240
Trying to guess
what he's thinking every day

75
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:05,390
is even more tiring than dealing with
Madam Shen back then.

76
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,700
His Majesty is ten thousand times better
than Madam Shen.

77
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,120
That's true.

78
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:12,319
At least he's young, good-looking,

79
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:13,240
and has a strong body.

80
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,400
His lips are soft

81
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,360
when he kisses.

82
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,600
Young Lady, you shouldn't say
such things out loud.

83
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:21,399
Go see if His Majesty
has finished his work.

84
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,700
Invite him to come over for dinner.

85
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,000
Mm.

86
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:23,879
I'll go right away.

87
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,319
Your Majesty, this is the latest report
from Tinglan Palace.

88
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:32,399
Mm.

89
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:36,279
At the third quarter of Shen hour,

90
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:38,439
Lady Shen carved a fox hairpin
and said...

91
00:04:41,230 --> 00:04:42,800
She said that being favored is useless,

92
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:44,100
that Your Majesty is difficult to please,

93
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,680
and that men...

94
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,720
That men are all useless.

95
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,160
What else did she say?

96
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,319
She also said

97
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,360
foxes are the truly loyal lovers.

98
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,980
They're faithful
to only one partner for life.

99
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:56,000
Foxes?

100
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,199
Nonsense.

101
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,439
That actually isn't nonsense.

102
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,639
I've heard such sayings
about foxes being loyal.

103
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:05,120
You mean

104
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:07,610
she wishes to spend her whole life
as husband and wife with me?

105
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,920
That's what you wish for too.

106
00:05:11,839 --> 00:05:13,360
It's not that I doubt her.

107
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,600
The unrest in the nation is one matter.

108
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:18,240
Whether Manshu Tears can be cured

109
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:19,199
is another.

110
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,319
I've walked on thin ice my whole life.

111
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:24,480
I may fall

112
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,560
and never stand up again one day.

113
00:05:27,079 --> 00:05:27,720
Your Majesty,

114
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,759
I'll definitely find the antidote.

115
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,519
It's been quite a while
since someone was sent to His Majesty.

116
00:05:35,519 --> 00:05:36,680
Why haven't they returned yet?

117
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,199
Your Highness.

118
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,040
Your Highness,

119
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:41,490
His Majesty won't be coming tonight.

120
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,000
He has gone to Lady Liu's.

121
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,720
You may leave.

122
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:46,480
Yes.

123
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,839
His Majesty must have gone there

124
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:51,079
for some important matter.

125
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,319
Perhaps

126
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,879
you should rest first.

127
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,480
What a waste of all this food

128
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,560
and this bowl of botuo noodles.

129
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:01,759
Sit down.

130
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,800
We'll eat together.

131
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,480
Allow me to serve you.

132
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,399
No need.

133
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,460
Serving a bowl of botuo noodles
isn't tiring.

134
00:06:08,879 --> 00:06:10,160
Don't be upset, Young Lady.

135
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,319
His Majesty cares about you the most.

136
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,079
I'm not upset.

137
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,920
I used up all the sadness
of this lifetime

138
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,319
in my previous life.

139
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:18,839
Also,

140
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,360
being sad over a man

141
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,959
is the most worthless thing of all.

142
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:25,519
You've always had your own mind.

143
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:26,680
Back when Master

144
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,890
arranged your marriage to
that broke Young Master Lu,

145
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,480
you helped the Lu family move

146
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,560
from a run-down shack
into a proper manor.

147
00:06:33,090 --> 00:06:34,560
You were never afraid of hardship,

148
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,759
but you shouldn't always have to suffer.

149
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:39,759
I hope you'll meet the right person

150
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,000
and live a good life.

151
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:43,240
Kind Handan,

152
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:44,920
thank you.

153
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,140
(Tinglan Palace)

154
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:53,260
♪A fair lady sighs, what eve is this?♪

155
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:54,800
Young Lady,

156
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,160
it's getting late.

157
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,759
Let's return to the room.

158
00:06:57,759 --> 00:06:59,160
His Majesty won't be coming tonight.

159
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,920
I'll sleep
after I finish carving the hairpin.

160
00:07:03,879 --> 00:07:05,439
I'll fetch you a cloak.

161
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,279
Sure.

162
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:08,300
♪The partridge's cry
is full of resentment♪

163
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:14,740
♪You do not know that nothing
is sweeter than a fleeting love♪

164
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:21,460
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

165
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:28,220
♪Bitter cold, bringing mist to the eyes♪

166
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:32,020
♪If we don't meet♪

167
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:35,580
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

168
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:38,759
Nian.

169
00:07:39,639 --> 00:07:41,240
Nian.

170
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:45,000
My Nian, you have grown up.

171
00:07:52,399 --> 00:07:53,160
Mother.

172
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:56,800
Mother,

173
00:07:57,639 --> 00:07:59,079
you finally came.

174
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,879
Yu's good.

175
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,319
He's good-looking,

176
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:07,160
clever, and filial.

177
00:08:07,519 --> 00:08:08,240
Mother,

178
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,800
who's Yu?

179
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:12,920
I begged Heaven for a chance

180
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,639
to let him meet you.

181
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,920
Yu

182
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,079
is Nangong Xuanyu.

183
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,319
Mother,

184
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,360
what are you talking about?

185
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,519
Nian,

186
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,319
I need to go now.

187
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,279
Take good care of yourself.

188
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,759
Mother.

189
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,639
Mother.

190
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,039
Mother,

191
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:38,799
don't go.

192
00:08:40,399 --> 00:08:41,200
Mother...

193
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,360
(Shen Nianzhi,)

194
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:50,480
(why do you always cry in your dreams?)

195
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,679
Your Highness.

196
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,879
I think I hear

197
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,720
someone playing the guqin.

198
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,440
Most likely some lonely soul
unable to sleep,

199
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,039
playing a tune in the night.

200
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:53,879
Your Highness, you're frail.

201
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,390
You shouldn't stay in the cold wind.

202
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,519
It's fine.

203
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,679
The music is beautiful.

204
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:08,480
When I first met him,

205
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:10,960
he stood under a tree

206
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,879
in plain robes.

207
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,840
He was thin as a pine.

208
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,399
But his eyes

209
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:20,879
shone like stars in the night sky.

210
00:10:21,759 --> 00:10:23,080
With a mere glance,

211
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,840
I fell for him.

212
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,480
It has been ten years,

213
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,519
but he has never once smiled at me.

214
00:10:36,159 --> 00:10:37,480
One day,

215
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,279
His Majesty will see
how good you truly are.

216
00:10:43,919 --> 00:10:45,080
Where's he now?

217
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,960
At Tinglan Palace.

218
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,919
Tinglan Palace again.

219
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,320
Is Shen Zhinian

220
00:10:57,559 --> 00:10:59,120
that good?

221
00:11:13,519 --> 00:11:14,519
Yu.

222
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,879
My mother came.

223
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,600
She said you were good-looking.

224
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,000
What did you call me?

225
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,480
Your Majesty.

226
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,559
What did you

227
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:36,679
call me?

228
00:11:38,279 --> 00:11:39,240
Oh.

229
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:40,639
I was asleep.

230
00:11:40,639 --> 00:11:41,639
I dreamed of my mother.

231
00:11:42,759 --> 00:11:44,080
She called you Yu.

232
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:46,400
She said you were good-looking.

233
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,840
Your mother?

234
00:11:48,639 --> 00:11:49,200
Mm.

235
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,120
Since I came to the capital,

236
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,679
I've never dreamed of my mother again.

237
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,759
She told me to stay away
from the capital

238
00:12:06,519 --> 00:12:07,840
and its bloodshed.

239
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:10,919
But I failed.

240
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,559
She probably

241
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:16,840
doesn't want to see me anymore.

242
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:23,890
The Dowager Consort
probably wishes to see you,

243
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:25,639
but the road is too long.

244
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,360
She has yet to arrive.

245
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,279
The road is long?

246
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:30,759
Mm.

247
00:12:31,279 --> 00:12:33,159
The imperial temple
sits high in the mountains.

248
00:12:34,279 --> 00:12:35,679
The journey is long,

249
00:12:36,279 --> 00:12:37,990
but the scenery along the way
is beautiful.

250
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,879
The Dowager Consort keeps stopping
to admire the sights.

251
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:43,320
That's why she hasn't appeared
in Your Majesty's dreams.

252
00:12:44,759 --> 00:12:47,200
It's difficult enough for a woman

253
00:12:47,879 --> 00:12:49,080
to travel such a long distance.

254
00:12:50,399 --> 00:12:51,679
Your Majesty must be patient.

255
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:53,600
Wait patiently for the Dowager Consort.

256
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,080
Let her enjoy

257
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,520
the scenery at her own pace.

258
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Shen Zhinian.

259
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,759
That may work on children.

260
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,879
I'm not a child.

261
00:13:08,159 --> 00:13:09,799
Your Majesty grew up too quickly.

262
00:13:10,679 --> 00:13:11,799
You may allow yourself

263
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:13,080
to be a child sometimes.

264
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:14,679
Children are weak.

265
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:19,159
I never want to be a child again.

266
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:23,600
Don't coax me like that anymore.

267
00:13:25,490 --> 00:13:28,350
The Dowager Consort didn't want
Your Majesty to get involved in bloodshed

268
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,700
because she was worried
about your safety.

269
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:33,840
Your Majesty,

270
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,120
you were born for greatness.

271
00:13:37,879 --> 00:13:38,679
You will surely

272
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,600
restore the glory of Daliang

273
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,159
and bring all lands to bow before you.

274
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:48,919
The Dowager Consort could see this.

275
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,200
She would be happy.

276
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,780
♪The world is gentle
only because of you♪

277
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:55,780
♪In the palace, through dawn and dusk,
who keeps a lamp burning♪

278
00:13:56,180 --> 00:14:01,900
♪Time silently scars those left behind♪

279
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:05,540
♪I walk through the palace
day and night, just for my beloved♪

280
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:08,940
♪All my tenderness is for you,
I'd stay alone for you♪

281
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:11,900
♪I don't ask for equality,
only that you hear me♪

282
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:24,400
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

283
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:31,360
♪Bitter cold, bringing mist to the eyes♪

284
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,360
♪If we don't meet♪

285
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:38,800
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

286
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:45,520
♪If we meet again,
the peaches will be warm♪

287
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:52,320
♪Spring breeze passes,
dancing through the years♪

288
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:59,000
♪Brewing longing,
remembering past lives♪

289
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:06,200
♪Hard to meet, and just as hard to part♪

290
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:13,080
♪Who planted the beans
that grew into lotuses?♪

291
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:19,200
♪Spring breeze passes,
composing the fleeting years♪

292
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:26,720
♪Clouds on Mount Wu,
no sails on the sea♪

293
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:33,560
♪Wanting to fold my heart
into a paper kite♪

294
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:40,280
♪But the ties are too tangled to sever♪

